      <h1>RTO12/Explorers’ Edge </h1>

      <h3>Welcome to the ‘SHARE YOUR CANADA CONTEST” from RTO12/Explorers’ Edge – the regional tourism organization for Algonquin Park, Almaguin, Loring-Restoule, Muskoka and Parry Sound, Ontario, Canada that is funded by the Ontario Ministry or Tourism, Culture & Sport.</h3>

      <h1>CONTEST TERMS & CONDITIONS</h1>
      <h3>Eligibility</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>The Share Your Canada contest is only open to Canadian citizens currently legally residing in the United States of America, England or Scotland who are at least 19 years of age or older. Entrants must hold a valid passport to qualify and be eligible to obtain all legal travel documentation required to travel to Canada.</li>
        <li>Explorers’ Edge reserves the right to disqualify contest entrants who submit low quality images or derogatory content.</li>
        <li>All entrants must be willing to submit email address and enter contest through designated online portal. </li>
        <li>All entrants must agree to appear in person at Muskoka Region upon agreed trip timeframe (July or August 2017) and to have their social content judged by the Regional Judge. </li>
        <li>Explorers’ Edge will cover costs for round-trip travel to and from Toronto’s Pearson International Airport for four (4) adults, one week (7 days) of driver-provided transportation to and from Pearson International Airport to the Explorers’ Edge region and to applicable activities, 1-week (7 days) of shared accommodations at a participating accommodations provider(s), 2 qualified activities and 1 pre-paid credit card in the amount of $500 Canadian to cover the costs of additional transport (taxis) and dining. Grand Prize winner and additional travelers will cover costs of all insurance, travel documents incidentals and additional travel/food/activities/food.</li>
        <li>There is no purchase necessary to enter this contest. </li>
        <li>You must be 19+ at the time of travel.</li>
      </ul>
      <h3>Qualifying Shared Memories of the Great Canadian Wilderness</h3>
      <p>
        Explorers’ Edge has broadly defined the concept of an ideal eligible great Canadian wilderness memory.
      </p>
      <p>
        Qualifying entrants must enter a memory that:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Took place somewhere in the great Canadian wilderness </li>
        <li>Is accompanied by a high resolution image</li>
        <li>Shows your pride in Canada and your passion for being Canadian </li>
      </ul>
      <h3>Sponsor</h3>
      <p>
        The Share Your Canada Contest is sponsored and administered by RTO12/Explorers’ Edge and its partners. Explorers’ Edge will use and show partner logos on all marketing and/or promotional material without notice. This photo/video contest is no way sponsored by, endorsed by, administered by, or associated with Facebook, Instagram or Twitter.
      </p>
      <h3>Entry Period</h3>
      <p>
        The Share Your Canada contest will officially open on February 23, 2017. Public voting will close May 21st, 2017.  Five finalists will be determined from highest vote tabulation on May 21, 2017 and the Grand Prize winner will be chosen and announced from among the finalists by the Regional Judge on May 22, 2017.
      </p>
      <h3>Submission</h3>
      <p>
        Your great Canadian wilderness memory can be entered in one way:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Through the Share Your Canada website: www.shareyourcanada150.ca Each submission must have the following:</li>
        <li>One high resolution .jpg, .jpeg, .png or .gif format photos (uploaded to the Share Your Canada website) and;</li>
        <li>A 250-word description of the memory and why you think it deserves to be voted as “most Canadian”</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        Please do NOT submit the following:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Content that violates or infringe upon another person’s rights, including but not limited to copyright</li>
        <li>Photo that includes people other than yourself unless you have their permission to post and share online</li>
        <li>Content that contains sexually explicit, nude, obscene, violent or other objectionable or inappropriate content.</li>
        <li>Photos and videos of a memory you do not own</li>
      </ul>
      <h3>How to Enter</h3>
      <p>
        All content must be submitted through the entry form on our dedicated contest website. Your submission must include all required fields, including name, email and other information about your Canadian memory.
You may enter one memory, one time only and you may not use an agency or automated system to enter. Sponsor reserves the right to reject any additional entries or entries that do not comply with the Contest Rules. By entering, you indicate your unconditional agreement to, and acceptance of, these Contest Rules and Sponsor’s decisions, which are final and binding. You cannot win a prize unless you comply with all requirements in these Contest Rules.
Entrants may be asked to supplement their submission (such as additional information about their entry or the highest resolution version of their photo/video content) at anytime during the entry period.
By entering this contest, all entrants hereby agree to allow Explorers’ Edge to use, royalty-free and nonexclusive, all submitted content and relevant personal information such as name and hometown, for use on website, social media, promotional and publicity materials in perpetuity.
      </p>
      <h3>Selection & Judging</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>All submissions will be reviewed by Explorers’ Edge staff and qualified entries will be posted to the Share Your Canada contest website where the public will be able to vote and share entries.</li>
        <li>Explorers’ Edge staff shall determine entry eligibility in its sole and absolute discretion.</li>
        <li>Public online voting will close on May 21, 2017 to determine the Five Finalists.</li>
        <li>The top finalists (decided by public votes) will then be judged by the Regional Judge to select one Grand Prize winner.</li>
        <li>The Regional Judge will base his decision on a combination of the quality of the memory pertaining to the great Canadian wilderness experience, positive public reaction to the memory, and the owner’s evident passion for being a Canadian.  Extra consideration will be given to memories that showcase Algonquin Park, Muskoka, Parry Sound or the geographical areas close by.</li>
        <li>The Regional Judge is: James Murphy, Executive Director of Explorers’ Edge </li>
        <li>The Grand Prize Winner will be announced on May 22, 2017 and has 7-days to accept this prize or a new winner will be selected from among the five finalists. This process will continue until the Grand Prize is accepted. If none of the five finalists accepts the Grand Prize after being awarded it, there will be no further selection of a winner.</li>
      </ul>
      <h3>Potential Winner/Finalist Requirements</h3>
      <p>
        Except where prohibited, a potential winner/finalists (Five Finalists and Grand Prize winner) may be required to complete and return an affidavit of eligibility, including proof of age, and liability/publicity release within 7-days of being contacted. If a potential winner fails to return these documents on time, an alternate potential winner may be selected in his/her place.
      </p>
